EXCUSE ME...

14
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:36,800
... MAY WE TROUBLE YOU FOR ASSISTANCE?

15
00:01:39,300 --> 00:01:41,200
Speakenzee Englishsky?

16
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,600
Oh...

17
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:43,800
Eh...

18
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:45,700
I'm sorry. Um...

19
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,800
For my family, please.

20
00:01:48,300 --> 00:01:50,100
We ask for your kind help.

21
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,800
MAY I HELP YOU, SIR?

22
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:53,700
YOU SPEAK RUSSIAN?

23
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:56,100
Well, only a little.

24
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,900
MY GRANDPA TAUGHT ME.

25
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:01,100
You a Russky too, Vera?

26
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,600
Go get 'em, rook.

27
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:05,500
THANK GOD...

28
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,800
.. I DON'T KNOW IF OUR CHAPERONES FOLLOWED US...

29
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:09,600
... WHAT IS THE PROTOCOL?

30
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:11,300
Whoa, sir.
I ain't fluent.

31
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:13,700
I got curses and toasts,
that's all.

32
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:15,900
Papa, please.

33
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:19,500
We surrender our passports.

34
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:22,500
we want to defect
to United States.

35
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,500
<i>The United States.</i>

36
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,500
You speak English... big time.

37
00:02:27,700 --> 00:02:31,300
I learned by watching American
television on the black market.

38
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,300
Don't tell my father.

39
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:36,500
You, uh, coming
from the prom?

40
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:38,800
Uh...

41
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,000
a concert.

42
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:41,900
This dress belonged
to my mother.

43
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:43,700
NADIA, WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

44
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,100
We'll, uh, call
the State Department

45
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:46,800
and get someone down here
to meet you.

46
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:50,500
Discuss political asylum.

47
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:58,200
You know, if you do this,
there's no going back.

48
00:03:04,700 --> 00:03:05,700
Yeah.

49
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:08,600
Welcome to the United States,
little man.

50
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:12,900
I am sorry.
He only knows police

51
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:15,300
in Russia, where
they can't be trusted.

52
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:17,300
Things are different here.

53
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:24,900
You call me, any time.

54
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:28,800
I'll help you out.

55
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:37,500
And, uh, for your, uh,
collection.

56
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:40,600
Philadelphia.

57
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,400
Our new home.

58
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:20,200
KOSLOV, N. DEC '89

59
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:33,900
I haven't responded
to a fight on the highway

60
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:35,400
since I was in uniform.

61
00:04:35,700 --> 00:04:37,000
Call came in from the district,

62
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,800
someone asking for me
by name.

63
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,300
I'll turn that face
into scrap metal!

64
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:42,500
I'll kill you first!

65
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:44,000
Your kind of crowd, Nick.

66
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:45,000
Who's the guy?

67
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:48,800
Do I know you?

68
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:51,500
Yeah, you said
I could call anytime.

69
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,500
I'm Dimitri.

70
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:03,600
Yeah, Koslov.
I remember.

71
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,000
What's going on?

72
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:07,500
This scum has my sister's bag.

73
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:08,700
This bag ain't even mine, man!

74
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:10,200
So where'd you get it,
tough guy?

75
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,400
Cousin Beamer.

76
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:12,400
Just denied parole.

77
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:14,100
His mama's giving
away his stuff.

78
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:16,400
Son of a bitch.

79
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:17,300
Know whose it is?

80
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:19,200
Nadia Koslov.

81
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:20,400
Who's she?

82
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:23,500
I was in the Ninth District
the night the family defected.

83
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:25,500
Four months later,
I was at her funeral.

