- Nikki, what are you doing?

524
00:23:33,100 --> 00:23:35,300
Warming up for three hours
on toe shoes.

525
00:23:35,500 --> 00:23:36,600
What does it look like?

526
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:37,800
An overdose.

527
00:23:39,500 --> 00:23:40,800
But you're good.

528
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:41,700
You're great.

529
00:23:41,700 --> 00:23:43,600
- You don't need this stuff.
- What I need is

530
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:45,400
for you to get
the hell out here!

531
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,100
I'm gonna go get some help.

532
00:23:48,100 --> 00:23:48,700
You're gonna
be all right...

533
00:23:48,700 --> 00:23:50,100
Bitch, if you get anyone,
I swear to God

534
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:51,400
you'll wish you hadn't.

535
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:03,300
Nadia consider
herself warned?

536
00:24:03,500 --> 00:24:04,600
I don't think so.

537
00:24:04,700 --> 00:24:05,500
That same week, Regis

538
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:07,700
instituted
a zero-tolerance drug policy

539
00:24:07,700 --> 00:24:09,200
and Nikki was expelled.

540
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:12,000
Well, how'd the prima
ballerina take it?

541
00:24:12,500 --> 00:24:15,600
If she had a heart,
it would've been broken.

542
00:24:26,900 --> 00:24:29,100
You were in
Phoebe Curtis's workshop?

543
00:24:29,300 --> 00:24:30,400
Sure was.

544
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:32,100
The best of the best.

545
00:24:32,100 --> 00:24:33,600
Couldn't find you
in the yearbook.

546
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:36,100
What happened between then
and graduation?

547
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:39,100
Regis wasn't preparing me
for the realities of the biz.

548
00:24:39,300 --> 00:24:40,200
So I quit.

549
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:41,400
You "quit," huh?

550
00:24:42,100 --> 00:24:43,300
So what's this?

551
00:24:46,500 --> 00:24:48,700
- Looks like
"Papers of Expulsion"?
- Yours.

552
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:51,500
Nadia rats you out for drugs,
and you end up here.

553
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:53,000
So where were you,
night she died?

554
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:54,300
Truth this time.

555
00:24:55,900 --> 00:24:57,500
I was too short
for a professional

556
00:24:57,500 --> 00:24:59,000
corps de ballet.

557
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:00,900
Everyone tried to tell me.

558
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:03,500
But I wouldn't listen.

559
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:05,700
I punished myself instead.

560
00:25:06,500 --> 00:25:07,700
Nothing an addict likes better

561
00:25:07,700 --> 00:25:09,700
- than someone else to blame it on.
- Trust me.

562
00:25:09,700 --> 00:25:11,800
My hatred was directed inward.

563
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:14,800
They had already kicked me out

564
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:16,400
when Nadia found me
in my dressing room.

565
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:18,700
We check with the school,
they gonna confirm that story?

566
00:25:18,700 --> 00:25:21,700
I could care less what
the Regis faculty say about me.

567
00:25:22,600 --> 00:25:24,900
Those losers couldn't do, teach,

568
00:25:25,300 --> 00:25:27,100
or keep their hands
to themselves.

569
00:25:31,200 --> 00:25:33,000
Think of the most painful

570
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:35,700
experience of your life.

571
00:25:36,900 --> 00:25:38,300
Boil it down...

572
00:25:39,300 --> 00:25:40,700
to one name.

573
00:25:42,300 --> 00:25:43,400
And when you're ready,

574
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,200
say it out loud.

575
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:47,800
Shout it,
if you have to.

576
00:25:48,100 --> 00:25:49,700
But it's so hard to choose.

577
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:53,600
I have to go.

578
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:07,400
You're holding
onto something, Nadia.

579
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:08,700
You've got
to let it go.

580
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:10,600
"Holding on"?

581
00:26:11,300 --> 00:26:12,700
I left my entire life behind.

582
00:26:12,700 --> 00:26:14,500
I have nothing left
to hold onto.

583
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:15,800
Except the hurt.

584
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:19,700
It's come right along with you.

585
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:25,000
Running away is not
the same thing as letting go.

586
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:26,600
I'm trying.

587
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:27,800
I've seen

588
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:30,700
brilliant performers
self-destruct.

589
00:26:31,100 --> 00:26:32,400
If you need my help...

590
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:36,400
I'll be there for you.

591
00:26:36,500 --> 00:26:37,500
Day or night.

592
00:26:38,300 --> 00:26:39,400
Okay.

593
00:26:43,600 --> 00:26:46,100
Elliot Glick took a special
interest in Nadia?

594
00:26:46,100 --> 00:26:47,900
Like a heat-seeking missile.

595
00:26:48,300 --> 00:26:48,800
What was in that

596
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:51,100
- little, brown bottle of his?
- I don't know.

597
00:26:51,100 --> 00:26:52,600
Aromatherapy stuff?

598
00:26:52,900 --> 00:26:54,100
What'd it smell like?

599
00:26:55,700 --> 00:26:57,000
Minty.

600
00:26:59,400 --> 00:27:01,500
Said you and Nadia
"didn't interact much."

601
00:27:01,500 --> 00:27:02,900
Want to revise
that statement?

602
00:27:05,900 --> 00:27:06,600
No.

603
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:10,800
- Been divorced twice already.
- Well, I don't see

604
00:27:10,800 --> 00:27:13,600
what my marital history
has to do with Nadia Koslov.

605
00:27:14,100 --> 00:27:15,900
Family court records
on their way.

606
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:17,200
Might give us some insight

607
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:18,600
to the cause
of all those breakups.

608
00:27:18,600 --> 00:27:20,400
Anything you want
to tell beforehand?

609
00:27:20,500 --> 00:27:21,600
I have nothing to hide.

610
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:23,500
Delivery invoice
from Heart Mart,

611
00:27:23,700 --> 00:27:25,700
your old neighborhood
health food store.

612
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:27,300
Read the highlighted part.

613
00:27:30,600 --> 00:27:31,700
"Oil of wintergreen."

614
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:34,700
- You know that it was toxic?
- I was careful with it.

615
00:27:36,300 --> 00:27:37,600
I used it for MEditating.

616
00:27:37,800 --> 00:27:40,600
Witnesses saw you applying it
to minors, including Nadia.

617
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:42,400
Getting handsy
with her afterwards.

618
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:44,000
I was teaching The Method.

619
00:27:44,300 --> 00:27:45,200
I was helping
my students

620
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:48,100
gain an emotional investment
in their work.

621
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:50,400
I gave my soul to those kids.

622
00:27:50,500 --> 00:27:52,200
You were making a pass.

623
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:54,000
And when she rejected you,
you made her pay.

624
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:55,700
I didn't kill Nadia.

625
00:27:58,300 --> 00:28:00,000
But I didn't protect her,
either.

626
00:28:10,700 --> 00:28:11,500
Nadia.

627
00:28:14,300 --> 00:28:15,200
Are you all right?

628
00:28:17,800 --> 00:28:18,900
Katya.

629
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,900
- Excuse me?
- Katya.

630
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:25,200
The name I would've said
if I had courage.

631
00:28:27,100 --> 00:28:28,000
Your mother.

632
00:28:30,400 --> 00:28:31,500
Come here.

633
00:28:39,700 --> 00:28:43,600
My father didn't let me go
to her funeral.

634
00:28:44,900 --> 00:28:47,000
He didn't even
let me cry for her.

635
00:28:48,700 --> 00:28:50,900
She was a big
deal soprano,

636
00:28:50,900 --> 00:28:55,200
so instead of mourning,
we practiced.

637
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:58,200
I'm sorry.

638
00:29:00,600 --> 00:29:03,800
Before we left, I wanted
to put roses on her grave.

639
00:29:04,500 --> 00:29:06,200
But now I never can.

640
00:29:09,100 --> 00:29:11,200
She would be
so proud of you.

641
00:29:13,800 --> 00:29:16,700
I just wish she could hear
what I sound like.

642
00:29:16,700 --> 00:29:19,100
Not in Russia, now.

643
00:29:20,400 --> 00:29:23,500
Well, she can.

644
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:25,600
Go ahead.

645
00:29:25,700 --> 00:29:27,100
LET HER HEAR WHAT YOU SING.

646
00:29:31,100 --> 00:29:34,800
* And I see your true colors *

647
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:37,800
* Shining through *

648
00:29:38,200 --> 00:29:42,300
* See your true colors *

649
00:29:42,300 --> 00:29:45,700
* That's why I love you *

650
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:52,000
* To let them show... *

651
00:29:53,500 --> 00:29:54,900
I stop by.

652
00:29:55,300 --> 00:29:56,500
You not at opera.

653
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:59,300
- They say you quit.
- Mr. Koslov...

654
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,200
Papa! Papa!

655
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:03,900
- Hold on!
- Why are you not working?

656
00:30:03,900 --> 00:30:04,800
I am!

657
00:30:04,800 --> 00:30:08,300
<i>In here,
with this podunkum,</i>

658
00:30:08,300 --> 00:30:09,600
<i>singing this khrenovyi</i>

659
00:30:09,600 --> 00:30:10,800
Amerikansky pop?

660
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:12,300
My final project is due tonight,

661
00:30:12,300 --> 00:30:14,100
and I will do it
the way that I want.

662
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:17,500
There is more
to life than opera.

663
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,500
Opera is our life.

664
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:24,200
I am not her, Papa.

665
00:30:25,900 --> 00:30:27,700
This crap school,

666
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:29,500
it ruins us.

667
00:30:29,500 --> 00:30:30,500
"Us"?

668
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,400
There is no us!

669
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:35,000
Just your dreams being shoved
down my throat.

670
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:44,900
A parent should encourage
his child's independence.

671
00:30:45,200 --> 00:30:48,400
But Leo took Nadia's growth
as a personal betrayal.

672
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:50,500
He chased her
down the hall.

673
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:52,500
That was the last
time I saw her.

674
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:57,900
Hey, Nick,
I've got something.

675
00:30:58,900 --> 00:31:02,000
A dean from St. Petersburg
Conservatory got back to us.

676
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:04,000
-  Yeah?
- Back in Russia, Leo Koslov

677
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:06,700
was a vocal coach
to some big careers,

678
00:31:06,700 --> 00:31:08,300
including his wife's.

679
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:10,900
- Katya.
- She gave him a nickname and it stuck,

680
00:31:10,900 --> 00:31:12,600
at least in opera circles.

681
00:31:14,700 --> 00:31:15,800
Zolotoi.

682
00:31:20,300 --> 00:31:21,600
The Golden One.

683
00:31:21,900 --> 00:31:24,600
Nadia was saying a name
with her last breath.

684
00:31:25,900 --> 00:31:27,300
And it was her father's.

685
00:31:51,100 --> 00:31:52,600
Open a bottle of vodka,

686
00:31:52,900 --> 00:31:54,900
can't leave the table
till it's done.

687
00:31:56,800 --> 00:31:58,200
Russian tradition?

688
00:31:58,200 --> 00:32:00,800
Grandpops, on my ma's side.

689
00:32:01,500 --> 00:32:02,700
My Deyda.

690
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:05,100
Left Russia and came
to this country alone.

691
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:10,700
He was 14.

692
00:32:11,700 --> 00:32:13,500
Wish I could ask him
more questions.

693
00:32:13,800 --> 00:32:15,500
Listen to more of his stories.

694
00:32:19,100 --> 00:32:21,600
TO THE WISDOM OF OUR ELDERS.

695
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:25,400
TO YOUR GRANDFATHER OF BLESSED MEMORY.

696
00:32:29,400 --> 00:32:32,900
Never knew about your career
in the old country, Leo.

697
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:35,000
Now I do.

698
00:32:36,800 --> 00:32:39,700
With her dying breath,
Nadia said your name.

699
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:42,600
The glory days
of your family,

700
00:32:43,500 --> 00:32:44,600
your career,

701
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:46,000
your marriage.

702
00:32:46,800 --> 00:32:48,100
Zolotoi.

703
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:51,800
Why did you lie to me?

704
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:56,900
I thought
I could leave the past behind.

705
00:32:58,300 --> 00:32:59,100
<i>Hamlet.</i>

706
00:32:59,100 --> 00:33:00,600
<i>Romeo and Juliet.</i>

707
00:33:00,700 --> 00:33:01,900
Lacrazy Borga.

708
00:33:01,900 --> 00:33:03,700
Lucrezia Borgia.

709
00:33:03,900 --> 00:33:05,100
The great operas.

710
00:33:05,100 --> 00:33:07,100
Stories all had death
by poisoning.

711
00:33:07,100 --> 00:33:09,500
Is that how you punished Nadia
for dishonoring you?

712
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:12,800
I am one who is punished
by fate.

713
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:14,400
You knew she had asthma.

714
00:33:14,700 --> 00:33:15,700
You knew it would be quick.

715
00:33:15,700 --> 00:33:17,400
Did that take the sting out
of what you were doing?

716
00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:18,900
You think
I did not suffer enough?

717
00:33:18,900 --> 00:33:21,000
Nadia made a tape
the day she died.

718
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:23,200
Empty case found
at the crime scene.

719
00:33:24,100 --> 00:33:25,200
You have it, Leo?

720
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:31,900
Nadia had asked me
to grieve for all we had lost.

721
00:33:33,700 --> 00:33:35,200
The last time I saw her,

722
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:37,500
she showed me the joy

723
00:33:37,500 --> 00:33:39,800
that is possible
on the other side of grief.

724
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:48,900
* It's a long day *

725
00:33:48,900 --> 00:33:51,500
* Living in Reseda *

726
00:33:51,500 --> 00:33:54,900
* There's a freeway *

727
00:33:54,900 --> 00:33:57,400
* RUNNING through their yard *

728
00:33:57,400 --> 00:34:00,600
* And I'm a bad girl *

729
00:34:00,600 --> 00:34:03,300
* 'Cause I don't even miss him *

730
00:34:03,300 --> 00:34:06,500
* Hey, I'm a bad girl *

731
00:34:06,500 --> 00:34:09,200
* For breaking his heart *

732
00:34:09,200 --> 00:34:10,400
* And I'm free *

733
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:12,200
<i>* Free fallin' *</i>

734
00:34:12,200 --> 00:34:15,100
<i>* Now I'm free fallin' *</i>

735
00:34:15,100 --> 00:34:17,100
* Free fallin' *

736
00:34:17,100 --> 00:34:21,100
<i>* Free fallin',
now I'm free fallin' *</i>

737
00:34:21,100 --> 00:34:23,100
* Hey, I'm free *

738
00:34:23,100 --> 00:34:27,200
<i>* And I'm free fallin',
now I'm free fallin' *</i>

739
00:34:27,200 --> 00:34:28,200
* Free fallin' *

740
00:34:28,200 --> 00:34:33,300
<i>* Now I'm free fallin',
now I'm free fallin' *</i>

741
00:34:33,300 --> 00:34:39,200
<i>* Va', pensiero,
sull'ali dorate *</i>

742
00:34:39,200 --> 00:34:45,000
<i>* Va', ti posa sui clivi,
sui colli *</i>

743
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:48,100
<i>* O veo lezza note pide molli *</i>

744
00:34:48,100 --> 00:34:51,200
<i>* Free fallin',
now I'm free fallin' *</i>

745
00:34:51,200 --> 00:34:57,200
<i>* L'au dolci del suo lo natal *</i>

746
00:34:57,200 --> 00:35:03,200
<i>* O mio Patria,
s  bella perduta *</i>

747
00:35:03,200 --> 00:35:08,800
<i>* O remembranza s  cara
e fatal *</i>

748
00:35:08,800 --> 00:35:10,500
* And I'm free *

749
00:35:10,500 --> 00:35:15,100
<i>* Free fallin',
now I'm free fallin' *</i>

750
00:35:15,100 --> 00:35:21,100
<i>* Now I'm free fallin',
now I'm free fallin' *</i>

751
00:35:21,100 --> 00:35:28,500
<i>* Now I'm free fallin',
now I'm free fallin', now... *</i>

752
00:35:33,900 --> 00:35:35,400
You know "Va Pensiero?"

753
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:37,700
From an opera
by Verdi.

754
00:35:38,100 --> 00:35:39,800
It's a famous song
about freedom

755
00:35:39,800 --> 00:35:43,100
and also of homesickness.

756
00:35:47,800 --> 00:35:48,900
The tape--

757
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:51,600
it was her final project

758
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:53,600
for the class that I cursed.

759
00:35:58,900 --> 00:36:00,300
She knew you loved her.

760
00:36:00,300 --> 00:36:02,700
But I never got a chance
to tell her that.

761
00:36:06,400 --> 00:36:08,800
Elliot Glick's divorce
records were a goldmine.

762
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:10,300
Glick's exes
had a lot to say

763
00:36:10,300 --> 00:36:13,100
about his extracurricular
activities.

764
00:36:13,500 --> 00:36:15,300
He have a history
with his students?

765
00:36:15,700 --> 00:36:16,900
Phoebe Curtis.

766
00:36:17,200 --> 00:36:18,700
Major player
in his second divorce.

767
00:36:18,700 --> 00:36:20,200
Ten years on and off.

768
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:21,500
Cornered his second wife

769
00:36:21,500 --> 00:36:23,600
in a parking garage
with a crowbar.

770
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:25,600
And that was just
her opening act.

771
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:26,800
Would have been threatened
by Nadia

772
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:28,500
once Glick had his eyes on her.

773
00:36:28,500 --> 00:36:30,500
Well, Glick brought
oil of wintergreen

774
00:36:30,500 --> 00:36:33,800
to Phoebe's apartment
for that acting thing.

775
00:36:35,300 --> 00:36:38,600
Date on the cassette case
is the day Nadia died.

776
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:41,600
Missing tape
was her final project.

777
00:36:42,500 --> 00:36:43,900
She might have gone
to Phoebe's house

778
00:36:43,900 --> 00:36:44,900
to hand it in personally.

779
00:36:44,900 --> 00:36:46,300
Phoebe lived two blocks

780
00:36:46,300 --> 00:36:49,000
from the subway
where Nadia was found.

781
00:36:50,400 --> 00:36:51,600
Get her down here.

782
00:36:54,100 --> 00:36:54,600
Want you to think

783
00:36:54,600 --> 00:36:57,700
of the most painful experience
